    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.32.13-14_0001a" />
                <note type="curatorial">133- 1                          Aly Collection</note>
                 
              <fw type="letterhead">  
                Skyrim Farm             <hi rend="caps">JOHN G. NEIHARDT</hi>
                  <lb/>
                Route 7
                <lb/>
                Columbia, Mo.
              </fw>
                
                <opener>
                <dateline>5-17-'61</dateline>
                
                
                <salute>Dear Bower:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I was delighted to hear from you!</p>
                
                <p>Many, many thanks for the article about that fine old fellow, Washalsie. I know quite a bit about him, but it's good to be vividly reminded of him again.</p>
                
                <p><hi rend="underline">Are</hi> you going to hunt books with me in Portland this summer, if and when I come out? 
                <hi rend="underline">That would be fun</hi>! I <hi rend="underline">do</hi> want to raid that bookstore &#8212;
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.32.13-14_0001b"/>
                <fw type="authorial">-2-</fw>
                
                <hi rend="underline">Carson's</hi>, isn't it? What pickings!!</p>
                
                <p>Lucile's speech was perfect &#8212; beautiful too, and it made me very very humble. I've heard appreciative remarks about it from a number of people.</p>
                
                <p>I'm hoping I may see you this summer. I want to.</p>
                <closer>
                <salute>Affectionately,</salute> <signed>John</signed>.
                </closer>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">13</fw>
            </div1>
            
            
            
